Major duties:

To operate the central / local control computer to monitor the operational status of all production facilities;
To make proper adjustment of production process;
To improve product quality and increase operation efficiency;
To assist shift-in-charge to coordinate manufacturing and maintenance activities;
To assist shift-in-charge to initiate appropriate emergency procedures to cope with different types of system failure; and
To carry out assigned duties during major equipment overhaul period.

Requirements:

Higher Diploma or Associate Degree in Applied Science or Engineering;
Minimum 1 year working experience in manufacturing industries;
Self-confident, out-going and energetic;
Strong communication and interpersonal skills;
Overnight shift duty is required;
Candidate with more experience will be considered as Process Control Engineer; and 
Fresh graduate will also be considered.

Duties:
The appointee will work on the development of functional PVD coatings on various substrates. He/she will work in a dynamic and efficient team which is responsible for R&D work, including experimental design, laboratory equipment operation, sample preparation, properties characterization, data analysis, performance testing, drafting proposals / meeting slides / reports / SOP / IP documents, in the following areas:

Designing and optimization on the coating formulation and PVD parameters, characterization on the properties of PVD coatings;
Incubating idea to explore the opportunity of cooperation with industry partners;
Scaling up process for trial production; and
Performing other duties assigned by supervisor. 


Requirements:

Master or PhD in Polymer Science, Chemistry, Material Science/Engineering or related disciplines;
Solid experiences on physical vapor deposition (PVD);
Experiences on characterization of mechanical properties;
Experiences on surface treatment and coating technologies will be an advantage;
Good command of spoken and written English and Chinese;
Good communication, presentation and interpersonal skills, ability of literature and patent review are needed;
Work independently and able to communicate in teamwork; and
Candidates with more experience will be considered as Senior Engineers.


Salary and Benefit:
We offer 5-day work, attractive remuneration package to the successful candidates. Salary will be commensurate with qualifications and experience. Medical and dental benefits as well as annual leave will be provided. We also offer an open, collaborative and friendly working environment as well as ample capacity for your professional development. Appointment will be offered on a contract basis, renewable subject to mutual agreement and performance.

