Duties

The appointee will be responsible for project implementation, including experimental design, laboratory equipment operation, sample preparation, properties characterization, performance testing, data analysis, and reporting. He/she will be responsible for:

Characterization and testing of rheological and mechanical properties of engineered materials modified with lightweight aggregates with fibers;
Develop formulations for concrete and mortar materials and conduct daily lab tests;
Testing of the performance, including fast setting, strength development, permeability, bonding, of the material that is tailored-made to the requirements of industrial partners;
Prepare project progress reports, meeting slides, and related documents;
Planning out field trials, developing scaling up and relevant mixing procedures of engineered construction materials;
Support scale up and commercialization of all R&D results for industrial partners;
Drive innovation projects of new products or new applications according to customer and project requirement;
Support the incubation of ideas to explore new cooperation opportunities with industrial partners; and
Perform other duties assigned by supervisor.
Requirements
Master or Ph.D. in Civil Engineering, Mechanical Engineering, Materials Science or related disciplines, focusing on advanced engineering materials and composites materials related technologies;
R&D experiences on materials/ products characterization technique, applying/ developing composite materials, nano-modification, and numerical simulation is preferable while fresh graduates will also be considered;
Prior experiences on advanced materials development/ deployment for building and construction related applications is an advantage;
